{"key":"processedPost-19495763","value":{"id":19495763,"first":19495424,"last":19515770,"when":1391102539,"utime":"01/30/14 07:22 PM","content":"Experience from myself and other growers have shown the point of diminishing returns with <i>P cubensis</i> starts at a substrate depth of around 3 to 4 inches if using coir, compost, manure, etc.&nbsp; With straw, you can use a much deeper substrate, but anything over 12\" or so runs the risk of the core becoming anaerobic and starting to rot.<br /><br />The age-old argument over whether two 4\" deep substrates will outperform one 8\" deep substrate will be hashed and re-hashed forever, but my money is on the two shallower ones.&nbsp; Experiment away.<br />RR","title":"Re: Mushroom Fruiting Patterns","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}